Analysis of the components of soot literally lead to the production of some of the first early commercial estrogen products. In the 18th century young boys were forced to sleep in soot (So your chimneys I sweep & in soot I sleep.) What was then is now. Issues persist in new forms

On a more cheerful (?) note, one is tempted to note that the reason chimney sweeps were seen as "lucky" in Europe is the same reason as why hermaphrodites were worshipped in Hindoo India and said to bring good fortune to those who see them.
